    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for an aggressive offensive showing today, led by **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (75.66) and **Gunnar Henderson** (75.34). **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** benefits from a favorable matchup against Simeon Woods Richardson, and while he faces a slight dynamic platoon disadvantage, his elite 0.389 xwOBA keeps his floor remarkably high. **Gunnar Henderson** remains a top-tier play due to his leadoff positioning and a solid park factor against Will Warren. However, the most explosive potential lies with **Josh Lowe**, who carries a 72.21 score; he is a priority start against Christian Scott, whose astronomical 15.44 xERA suggests a massive breakout opportunity for our hitters. **Drake Baldwin** and **Kyle Tucker** also offer elite stability, both clearing the 72-point threshold with strong matchups against pitchers with xERAs exceeding 4.60.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was leaving **Josh Jung** (60.35) out of the starting nine. He narrowly missed the cut behind **Heliot Ramos**, who earns the nod due to his elite sprint speed and a high-leverage leadoff spot against the lefty Shane McClanahan. Because stolen bases are our scarcest category, **Heliot Ramos**'s speed profile\u2014combined with the favorable 100% stolen base opportunity noted in his projection\u2014ultimately edged out the slightly higher raw projection of **Josh Jung**. While **Marcell Ozuna** also flirted with a starting role at 59.72, the combination of **Nolan Schanuel**\u2019s favorable matchup against the porous Christian Scott and the defensive utility requirements kept him on the bench. \n\nRisks for today center primarily on the \"Lineup Pending\" status for all starters, which introduces volatility to our assumed batting order gains. Specifically, **Dominic Smith** is the weakest link in our lineup (55.61); although he draws a favorable matchup against Jose Quintana, his L/L platoon disadvantage and lower lineup positioning make him a primary candidate for a quick leash should defensive replacements or pinch-hitters become necessary. We are effectively betting on the soft matchup against Christian Scott to carry the bottom of our order, so monitor the weather closely, as any wind shifts could impact the scoring potential for **Nolan Schanuel** and **Josh Lowe** as the afternoon progresses.",
